riding around in these zodiacs.

00:06:32.770 --> 00:06:36.330
Before we got going we
were talking about a polarizing filter.

00:06:36.330 --> 00:06:42.270
The only filter
that I use outside is a polarizing filter.

00:06:42.270 --> 00:06:45.559
Polarizing
filter reduces glare on water, glare on ice,

00:06:45.559 --> 00:06:48.809
glare on
windows, glare on leaves, but it could also

00:06:48.809 --> 00:06:51.759
make your
pictures look sharper because it cuts down

00:06:51.759 --> 00:06:55.389
on the
reflections of the moisture in the atmospheric

00:06:55.389 --> 00:06:56.389
haze.

00:06:56.389 --> 00:06:58.469
It's the only filter I use outside.

00:06:58.469 --> 00:07:01.479
I used to use
gradual filters that are half dark on top

00:07:01.479 --> 00:07:04.360
and gradually
go clear on the bottom unless you hold them

00:07:04.360 --> 00:07:07.529
upside down [chuckles lightly]
and it's the opposite way, but that's the

00:07:07.529 --> 00:07:11.189
only filter I
use for my travel photography.

00:07:11.189 --> 00:07:14.669
If I'm doing a
waterfall, I'll use a neutral density filter.

00:07:14.669 --> 00:07:16.610
